column5: Got out with a buddy in his hut a couple weeks ago. Had a great day in 69 ft of water. I think the days total was 4 lakers and 6 or 7 whitefish.  http://www.youtube.com/user/TheVirtualAngler?feature=mhum  Lakers came on a #12 treble with a 1/8oz split shot up 6" from a lively shiner. Most of the whitefish came on spreader tip-up rig.  Hope the ice holds up for some fishing next week.  Cheers, Andrew
Great report and video Andrew Thanks for sharing!!! Leechman
What are they???????  They are Herring. good report and video.
